White House Chief of Staff Jeff Zients and senior officials met with the Welcome.US CEO Council, a group of CEOs from various industries, to discuss the expansion of lawful pathways for people seeking safety and refuge in the United States. The Welcome.US CEO Council is a nonpartisan, public-private partnership that aims to help communities welcome newcomers arriving through these pathways. The meeting focused on ways to support newcomers and scale innovations in employment, mentorship, delivery of goods and services, and community engagement. Participants also discussed the immediate needs of refugees and asylum seekers, with some companies committing to take actions to address these needs. The meeting emphasized the importance of public-private partnerships in responding to the global displacement crisis and committed to strengthening this partnership to ensure the successful integration of newcomers into their new communities.